briefTitle: Primary Study to Demonstrate Non-inferiority and Immunogenicity of GSK Biologicals' Meningococcal Vaccine 134612
officialTitle: Non-inferiority of GSK Biologicals' Meningococcal Vaccine 134612 Given Concomitantly With GSK Biologicals' Twinrix™ Versus 134612 Alone and Twinrix™ Alone in Healthy Subjects Aged 11 Through 17 Years.
summary: This study will demonstrate the non-inferiority of GSK Biologicals' meningococcal vaccine 134612 when given in an experimental co-administration versus vaccine 134612 alone and versus the experimental co-administration alone in healthy subjects aged 11 through 17 years. There will be 3 groups in this study.

primaryOutcome.measure: Meningococcal Polysaccharide A Serum Bactericidal Antibodies/Assay, Using Baby Rabbit Complement for Assay (rSBA-MenA), rSBA-MenC, rSBA-MenW-135 and rSBA-MenY Titers
primaryOutcome.timeFrame: At 1 month after vaccination with Nimenrix vaccine (Month 1)
